This walkthrough demonstrates the high-fidelity restoration of the Transactions module, matching the provided screenshot reference while leveraging the power of Batch Ingestion and adaptive layouts.

## High-Fidelity UI Restoration
The Transactions grid has been fully reconciled with the V5 "Purple Era" aesthetic.

### Signature Styling
- **Purple Header Card**: Implemented the deep purple (`#9333ea`) header theme with high-contrast white bold text.
- **Forensic Filtering**: Added integrated search filters directly into the header row for immediate drill-down capability.
- **"TXN" Source Pills**: Teal Pills are back for document identifiers, providing immediate visual classification of data sources.

### Vertical Adaptive Layout ("No Bibs")
- The stage and grid container now utilize full-screen flex logic. 
- The grid is glued to the viewport bottom, ensuring a professional, edge-to-edge spreadsheet experience regardless of screen scale.

## Multi-File Batch Ingestion
The upload zone has been hardened for high-volume document workflows.

- **Drop Bucket**: The entire dashed zone is now an interactive bucket supporting drag-and-drop and multi-file selection.
- **Iterative Forensic Scan**: The progress UI now tracks batch progress (e.g., `[1/3] Forensic Scan: Jan_Statement.pdf`) to provide real-time feedback during large forensic reconstructions.

